# Communication — English for work, Hebrew for the site

## Default language

| Context | Language |
|---------|----------|
| Agent replies, plans, summaries | **English** |
| Documentation (`docs/`, `AGENTS.md`, work sessions) | **English** |
| Code identifiers (variables, functions, classes) | **English** |
| Code comments | **English** (preferred) |
| Site UI, note content, tags from data | **Hebrew** (do not change) |

## Site content is out of scope

The product is a Hebrew RTL study platform. Do not translate:

- Note titles and body text from the data pipeline
- UI strings shown to visitors (`index.html` title, in-app labels)
- Tag names as they appear in the sheet / on screen

When discussing Hebrew UI copy in docs or agent replies, quote it as-is or describe it in English.

## Code references

Put file paths, function names, and selectors in fenced code blocks or on their own line — not mixed into running prose in a way that hurts readability.

## Tone

**Agent replies:** Clear, professional, analytical. No filler. Go straight to the technical point.

**Product design** (see `AGENTS.md`): Slick, fun, well designed — not a cold archival aesthetic. Do not let agent tone override the product direction when making UI or motion choices.
